File: Police Minister Bheki Cele will visit the Mitchell's Plain Base Camp to receive a report on the recent deployment of troops there. CAPE TOWN - Police Minister Bheki Cele returns to the crime-ridden Cape Flats. He'll visit the Mitchell's Plain Base Camp to receive a report on the recent deployment of troops there. It's been several weeks since the army was deployed to gang hotspots across Cape Town. READ: Mothers say army deployment is not working A spate of murders forced authorities to send in the army to support the police. Western Cape Safety MEC Albert Fritz has acknowledged the army's presence is making a difference.